# CCNA LAB 02 — PVST+ Per-VLAN Load Balancing

## Objective

Build a Layer 2 campus topology using PVST+ where:

* Distribution Switch 1 becomes ROOT for VLAN 10
* Distribution Switch 2 becomes ROOT for VLAN 20
* VLAN 30 uses default election
* Different VLANs take different physical paths
* Observe STP blocked ports per VLAN
* Verify traffic forwarding behavior
* Break one uplink and observe reconvergence

This lab teaches:

* PVST+ behavior
* STP root bridge manipulation
* Layer 2 path optimization
* VLAN-specific forwarding decisions
* Redundancy and failover behavior

