# BREAK TEST — SIMULATE UPLINK FAILURE

# Shutdown DSW1 uplink to ASW2

## DSW1

```cisco
configure terminal

interface g0/3
 shutdown

end
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# OBSERVE FAILOVER

Run immediately:

```cisco
show spanning-tree vlan 10
```

Expected:

* Previously blocked port transitions to forwarding
* Traffic reroutes through DSW2

Test ping again:

```bash
ping 10.10.10.20
```

You should see:

* 1–2 dropped packets
* Connectivity restored automatically

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# FIX THE FAILURE

## DSW1

```cisco
configure terminal

interface g0/3
 no shutdown

end
```

Wait for STP reconvergence.

